== BOM Project

A simple web application (rails) to play with temperature data provided by the Australian Bureau 
of Meteorology.

Provides graphs of temperature in Australian Local cities, provides a data collection
point for local temperature sensors (such as in an office), and provides graphs
of local temperature compared to capital city temperature.

== Jumpstart

Assumes you have git installed and a viable Ruby on Rails environment, version 2.3.5.

1. Checkout code.
  >git clone git://github.com/jbrownlee/bom.git
2. Install required ruby gems.
  >sudo gem install json  
3. Configure database.
  >cd bom
  >rake db:setup 
4. Run.
  >script/server
5. Test (in a browser) 
  > http://localhost:3000


